{"key":"post-11865931","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11865931</id>\n<content>You'll want to use about 550 to 600 ml for those 20 dishes. 3 1/2 tablespoons of FP pre-mix is correct for that amount of water.&amp;nbsp; I'd suggest a 750ml whiskey bottle for the agar.&amp;nbsp; The long neck makes it a lot easier to pour, and the smaller diameter opening makes it less likely that contaminants will enter as your pour.&amp;nbsp; Drill a hole in the lid, and then place a piece of tyvek over the bottle before screwing the lid on.&amp;nbsp; Cover with foil and sterilize 45 minutes at 15 psi.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11865945</next>\n<prev>11865838</prev>\n<first>11865179</first>\n<last>13457824</last>\n<when>1264020069</when>\n<utime>01/20/10 10:41 PM</utime>\n</post>"}